main event: The report contains details of a UFO sighting reported to the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book program.
interesting points: The object was described as silver, orange, green, and white in color, with a thin dome on top and a light on the bottom.
The object moved quite rapidly and silently, and was observed for about 30 minutes.
The observer was unsure if the sighting was of a satellite during the last few minutes.
The report includes a handwritten note comparing the brightness of the object to a common object.
The report contains a sketch or diagram depicting the shape and motion of the object.
sighted object: A silver, shiny, and bright object with a thin dome and a light on the bottom
photographs: No photographs, only a sketch or diagram
